### Pinpointing a single definition

WRONG:
```
Grep: "func.*CreateUser" in ./src/      ÔćÉ VIOLATION: used Grep before vfs
Read: user_service.go L1-200            ÔćÉ VIOLATION: reading whole file
```

RIGHT:
```
CallMcpTool(server: "user-user-vfs", toolName: "search", arguments: { "paths": ["./src"], "pattern": "CreateUser" })
  Ôćĺ src/services/user.go:42: func CreateUser(name string, email string) (*User, error)

Read: src/services/user.go L42-78
```

### When Grep IS the right first tool (skip vfs)

```
Grep: "INVALID_API_KEY" in ./internal/     ÔćÉ string literal inside function body
Grep: "database_url" in ./*.env            ÔćÉ non-code file
Read: handlers/upload.go L42-60            ÔćÉ user gave exact file path
```

## Supported File Types

| Language        | Extensions                              |
|-----------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Go              | `.go`                                   |
| JavaScript      | `.js`, `.mjs`, `.cjs`, `.jsx`           |
| TypeScript      | `.ts`, `.mts`, `.cts`, `.tsx`           |
